arch 2020, Charnas announced she tested positive for COVID-19 after using her personal connections to get a COVID-19 test at a time when limited tests were available.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/goatsandsoda/2020/03/26/821582951/is-loss-of-smell-and-taste-a-symptom-of-covid-19-doctors-want-to-find-out|title=Is Loss Of Smell And Taste A Symptom Of COVID-19? Doctors Want To Find Out|website=NPR.org|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nypost.com/2020/03/17/influencer-uses-personal-connections-to-get-coronavirus-test/|title=Influencer uses personal connections to get coronavirus test|last=Dellatto|first=Marisa|date=2020-03-17|website=New York Post|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> She received criticism for going against CDC guidelines by not self-quarantining and by traveling with her family to the Hamptons eight days after her diagnosis.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.indy100.com/article/coronavirus-influencer-arielle-charnas-breaks-self-isolation-quarantine-9440396|title=Influencer Arielle Charnas slammed for going on Hamptons trip after revealing she has coronavirus in test she got from a 'doctor friend'|last=Staples|first=Louis|date=April 1, 2020|work=Indy100|accessdate=2 April 2020}}</ref> Subsequently, Nordstrom further disassociated themselves from Charnas by announcing \"Our Partnership with Arielle Charnas ended in 2019. We have no foreseeable Something Navy collaborations\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/stephaniemcneal/arielle-charnas-coronavirus-instagram-controversy|title=How Influencer Arielle Charnas Became The Face Of \"Privilege In The Age Of The Coronavirus\"|website=BuzzFeed News|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> The New York Post labelled her a \"Covidiot\" and Vanity Fair (magazine) questioned if her decisions during the Pandemic would be the end of her \"Influencer\" career.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nypost.com/2020/04/02/covidiot-blogger-arielle-ch